text: 743 (seven hundred [and] forty three) is the natural number following 742 and preceding 744. It is a prime number. 743 is a Sophie Germain prime, because 2 × 743 + 1 = 1487 is also prime. There are exactly 743 independent sets in a four-dimensional (16 vertex) hypercube graph, and exactly 743 connected cubic graphs with 16 vertices and girth four. ==References== Category:Integers
title: 743 (number)
